BOGOTA &ndash; Colombia&#39;s coal output rose 3% to 22.2-million tonnes in the first quarter of this year, compared with the same period in 2016, the national mining agency said in a statement on Tuesday. The Andean nation, the world&#39;s fifth-largest coal exporter, produced 21.5-million tonnes in the same period a year ago, the ministry said. The sector is seeking to produce 95-million tonnes this year. The biggest players in Colombia&#39;s coal industry are Drummond, Glencore, Murray Energy&#39;s Colombia Natural Resources, and Cerrejon, which is jointly owned by BHP Billiton, Anglo American and Glencore.